Workshop Outline ...
1. Install and Setup: Installing Python. How do I run a
Python script? Jupyter Notebooks.
2. Handling Data: Reading and writing data. Dealing
with multiple files. Introduction to Pandas.
3. Visualisation: Introduction to Matplotlib. Scatterplots,
boxplots and histograms. Subplots, insets and trendlines.
Creating paper and thesis ready figures.
4. Advanced Pandas: Filtering and formatting. Merging
and concatenating. Get data straight from the web.
5. Putting it all together: Step-by-step examples using
authentic datasets. Doing cool stuff with YOUR data.
6. Pro tools for research: Git and GitHub. Plotly (interactive
graphs). Python for Latex.
Create high quality graphs and figures for your own publications.
Build tools to automate your analysis and make life easier.
